1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,367
What would you do if your apartment was one room bigger than it used to be?

2
00:00:03,317 --> 00:00:05,817
Mark is living that exact problem right now.

3
00:00:05,817 --> 00:00:08,461
He moved into a small one bedroom in November.

4
00:00:08,461 --> 00:00:09,903
Nothing special.

5
00:00:09,903 --> 00:00:14,519
Kitchen, bath, bedroom, living room, and a short hallway with a closet at the end.

6
00:00:14,519 --> 00:00:18,423
He has walked that hallway, by his own count, more than a thousand times.

7
00:00:18,423 --> 00:00:20,509
He knows every floorboard creak.

8
00:00:20,509 --> 00:00:22,855
Last Tuesday he comes home from work.

9
00:00:22,855 --> 00:00:24,480
Same as always.

10
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,442
Drops his bag by the door.

11
00:00:26,442 --> 00:00:28,096
Kicks his shoes off.

12
00:00:28,096 --> 00:00:30,750
Walks down the hallway to put his coat in the closet.

13
00:00:30,750 --> 00:00:32,615
Except the closet is gone.

14
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:34,307
In its place is a door.

15
00:00:34,307 --> 00:00:36,875
A heavy white paneled door with a brass handle.

16
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:39,480
It looks like it has been there since the building was built.

17
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:42,057
The wood matches the rest of the apartment perfectly.

18
00:00:42,057 --> 00:00:44,259
He stands there for fifteen minutes.

19
00:00:44,259 --> 00:00:45,576
Just staring.

20
00:00:45,576 --> 00:00:47,567
He walks back to the front door.

21
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:49,173
Walks forward again.

22
00:00:49,173 --> 00:00:50,519
Same door.

23
00:00:50,519 --> 00:00:52,884
He pulls up the floor plan in his lease.

24
00:00:52,884 --> 00:00:55,096
The hallway should be five feet long.

25
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:56,711
He gets a tape measure.

26
00:00:56,711 --> 00:00:58,673
It is now eleven feet long.

27
00:00:58,673 --> 00:01:01,576
Six extra feet of apartment that were not there yesterday.

28
00:01:01,576 --> 00:01:03,115
He tries the handle.

29
00:01:03,115 --> 00:01:04,182
Locked.

30
00:01:04,182 --> 00:01:05,875
He checks his keychain.

31
00:01:05,875 --> 00:01:07,538
There are four keys.

32
00:01:07,538 --> 00:01:08,875
Front door.

33
00:01:08,875 --> 00:01:10,201
Mailbox.

34
00:01:10,201 --> 00:01:11,394
Laundry.

35
00:01:11,394 --> 00:01:12,865
And a fourth key.

36
00:01:12,865 --> 00:01:14,099
Smaller.

37
00:01:14,099 --> 00:01:15,173
Older.

38
00:01:15,173 --> 00:01:16,807
Brass like the handle.

39
00:01:16,807 --> 00:01:19,826
He has no memory of the landlord ever giving him this key.

40
00:01:19,826 --> 00:01:21,480
He calls the landlord.

41
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,817
No answer.

42
00:01:22,817 --> 00:01:24,682
He calls the building manager.

43
00:01:24,682 --> 00:01:25,980
Voicemail.

44
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:27,942
He knocks on his neighbor's door.

45
00:01:27,942 --> 00:01:30,971
The woman next door has lived in the building for twenty years.

46
00:01:30,971 --> 00:01:34,288
Mark asks her, has your apartment ever, you know, grown?

47
00:01:34,288 --> 00:01:36,634
The neighbor stares at him for a long time.

48
00:01:36,634 --> 00:01:39,451
And then says, quote, you found the door.

49
00:01:39,451 --> 00:01:41,913
She closes her door without another word.

50
00:01:41,913 --> 00:01:43,836
Mark went back to his apartment.

51
00:01:43,836 --> 00:01:45,730
Put a chair in front of the door.

52
00:01:45,730 --> 00:01:47,817
Pushed his dresser against the chair.

53
00:01:47,817 --> 00:01:49,461
Slept on the couch.

54
00:01:49,461 --> 00:01:52,423
He says he hears something on the other side of the door at night.

55
00:01:52,423 --> 00:01:53,721
Not knocking.

56
00:01:53,721 --> 00:01:54,807
Breathing.

57
00:01:54,807 --> 00:01:55,980
Slow.

58
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:57,153
Patient.

59
00:01:57,153 --> 00:01:59,798
Like whatever is in there has all the time in the world.

60
00:01:59,798 --> 00:02:02,394
He posted last night asking for advice.

61
00:02:02,394 --> 00:02:04,576
Some commenters said burn the key.

62
00:02:04,576 --> 00:02:06,346
Some said try the key.

63
00:02:06,346 --> 00:02:11,105
One person, claiming to live in the same building, replied in all caps, do not open it.

64
00:02:11,105 --> 00:02:12,855
They never replied again.

65
00:02:12,855 --> 00:02:15,576
Mark says he's going to wait until morning to decide.

66
00:02:15,576 --> 00:02:18,403
Some of us in the comments don't think he has until morning.

67
00:02:18,403 --> 00:02:20,163
We'll know when he updates.

68
00:02:20,163 --> 00:02:21,644
If he updates.

69
00:02:21,644 --> 00:02:23,913
Subscribe so you don't miss part two.

